Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.92,0:00:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Conan Edogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.27,0:00:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school student Shinichi was forced\Nto take a drug that shrunk him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.50,0:00:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although smaller,\Nmy intelligence remains the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.96,0:00:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I solve cases not even adults can!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.83,0:00:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait!\NToday's Conan is a one-hour special!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.43,0:00:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Piano Sonata "Moonlight" Murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:21.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century in 100 years{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.83,0:00:27.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When told to cry, I laughed instead{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.03,0:00:39.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century\Nin a long, long time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.18,0:00:45.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're leaping into a wide open world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:52.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The things I tried to\Nunderstand as a child{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.34,0:00:58.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}remain a mystery even as an adult{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:04.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm neither a hotshot\Nnor especially great{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.89,0:01:11.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I understand is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.19,0:01:16.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's neither an answer nor the truth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:23.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I have faith in is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.29,0:01:28.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That and nothing else {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.22,0:01:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Piano Sonata "Moonlight" Murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.78,0:02:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does the famous detective Kogoro\NMori have to go to a stupid island
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.82,0:02:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when he could be spending his\Ntime at a flower viewing party?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.75,0:02:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all because of that letter\NI got a week ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.46,0:02:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the night of the next full moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.96,0:02:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shadows will once again begin to\Ndisappear from Tsukikage Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.92,0:02:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Investigate. Keiji Aso.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.38,0:02:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.26,0:02:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two days until the next full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.72,0:02:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've transferred half a million\Nto your bank account.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had best come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.98,0:02:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! Who the heck are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.85,0:02:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keiji Aso from Tsukikage Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.94,0:02:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait! Hello?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.86,0:02:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't even bother for me\Nto accept him as a client or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.45,0:02:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's to complain about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.70,0:02:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least we get to relax\Non a small island near Izu!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.49,0:02:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.61,0:02:54.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukikage Island
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.45,0:02:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keiji Aso...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:03:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anyone\Nby that name in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.91,0:03:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look harder, could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.45,0:03:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a letter from him\Nright here, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's not in the list of residents,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.08,0:03:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I just moved to this island,\Nso I don't know that much about--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief, it seems that these people\Nhave been hired by a resident here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.34,0:03:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hired?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.18,0:03:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.\NBy someone named Keiji Aso...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.52,0:03:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Did you say Keiji Aso?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.69,0:03:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible!\NHe's been dead for over 10 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a famous pianist who was born\Nand raised on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.38,0:03:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the night of a full moon,\N12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.55,0:03:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was his first time home\Nin a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.59,0:04:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he held a concert in\Nthe town's community center.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.39,0:04:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But afterwards, he suddenly shut his family\Nand himself inside their home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.18,0:04:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and lit the place on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.60,0:04:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He allegedly stabbed his wife\Nand daughter to death
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.98,0:04:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then continued to play\Nthe piano as the fire raged on,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.82,0:04:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,almost as if he was\Npossessed by something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beethoven's piano sonata...\N"Moonlight."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.50,0:04:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter from a dead man...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a nasty prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not necessarily the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your fee was paid, plus the letter\Nwas postmarked from this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.34,0:04:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet someone on the island wants\Nyou to look into Keiji Aso's affairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.14,0:04:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.76,0:04:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mayor here used to\Nbe a good friend of his,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.89,0:04:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe he can tell us something!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.02,0:04:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.15,0:04:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said the mayor's over\Nat the community center, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, Kenta-kun. Make sure\Nto keep warm when you sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I will! Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.28,0:05:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.20,0:05:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the community center?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.12,0:05:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You turn that corner\Nand then keep going straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, are you folks from Tokyo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We got\Noff the ship just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I live in Tokyo too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this island is so much nicer,\Nwouldn't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.09,0:05:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The air's fresh, and it's nice and quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.43,0:05:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Protect the island's fishing industry!\NVote for Masato Shimizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.93,0:05:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe not too quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.44,0:05:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mayoral election\Nis coming up, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.77,0:05:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mayoral election, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.73,0:05:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The candidates are Shimizu-san,\Nwho represents the fishermen,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.82,0:05:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,current mayor Kuroiwa-san,\Nwhose popularity is dwindling as of late,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.74,0:05:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Kawashima-san,\Nthe wealthiest man on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My patients have been telling me\Nthat Kawashima-san will probably--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.66,0:05:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's alright, Nurse. We're not really\Nthat interested in the election...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That's Doctor Narumi Asai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.34,0:05:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I have an actual license, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're a doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.63,0:06:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you folks are headed\Nto the community center,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.80,0:06:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can meet the three of them there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.68,0:06:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight they're holding a 3rd-year\Nmemorial for Kameyama-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,our previous mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your previous mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.94,0:06:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A 3rd-year memorial?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.52,0:06:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let the mayor\Ncontinue his reign of terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.15,0:06:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let the mayor\Ncontinue his reign of terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.03,0:06:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.36,0:06:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}How dare they do this on the night\N{\a6}of the previous mayor's memorial?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.78,0:06:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}They're really getting on my nerves!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.83,0:06:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Hirata! What're you doing?!\N{\a6}Shut them up already!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let the mayor continue\Nhis reign of terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.13,0:06:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.84,0:06:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is what okay, Shuichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.72,0:06:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}They're saying this election ain't\N{\a6}looking so good for your old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Indeed. It would seem the citizens\N{\a6}favor me the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.44,0:06:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's only because\Nyou know how to use money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.65,0:07:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which I learned from you, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a man here\Nwho wants to see the mayor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.99,0:07:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it, at a time like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A detective from Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? A detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, how long are\Nthey going to make me wait?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.37,0:07:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.80,0:07:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A piano...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.59,0:07:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What a huge room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.76,0:07:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the rear of the community center\Nis on the water's edge...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.27,0:07:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This piano sure is dirty...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.77,0:07:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd think they could at least\Nclean it once in a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.78,0:07:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the cursed piano that\NAso-san played the day he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cursed? Give me a break...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.62,0:07:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aso-san wasn't the only one!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:07:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same thing happened\Nto the last mayor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Isamu Kameyama-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.21,0:08:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the person they're holding\Nthe memorial for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.04,0:08:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It happened 2 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the night of a full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.68,0:08:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was passing by the community center,\Nwhich should have been empty,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.14,0:08:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I heard the sounds of\Na piano coming from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I called out to see who\Nwas there, the music stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.44,0:08:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside, I found Kameyama-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.07,0:08:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had died of a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.07,0:08:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the music he had been\Nplaying before he died
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.99,0:08:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was the same piece Aso-san had\Nperformed in the fire: "Moonlight."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, this piano came to\Nbe known as the Cursed Piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.84,0:08:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.80,0:08:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems normal enough to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.14,0:08:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, please wait by the front door\Nuntil the memorial is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.81,0:09:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Narumi-san! Are you\Ngoing to the memorial?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.69,0:09:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Kameyama-san was the first person\NI autopsied when I came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I would burn\Nsome incense in his honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is Shimizu-san.\NI happened to meet him on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.24,0:09:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, my name's Shimizu.\Nlt's nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.59,0:09:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kawashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.05,0:09:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hired a detective to dig up\Nsome dirt on me, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.72,0:09:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Running away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.55,0:09:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.44,0:09:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.40,0:09:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That piano should have remained\Nunused for years now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it produced a perfect sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.82,0:09:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must be tuning it secretly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.61,0:09:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For some purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what exactly was\Nthat letter trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.63,0:10:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This song!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.09,0:10:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Moonlight! Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.80,0:10:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.14,0:10:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kawashima-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.22,0:10:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.40,0:10:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.61,0:10:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.24,0:10:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Contact the local police station!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.11,0:10:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.11,0:10:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi. Please inspect the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.41,0:10:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.04,0:10:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That letter warned that another\Nperson on Tsukikage Island
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.75,0:10:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would die on the night of a full moon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.25,0:10:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the curse!\NIt's the curse of the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.22,0:11:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no curse. It's this tape recorder\Nthat's playing the music.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.89,0:11:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was a murder designed to resemble\Nthe previous two incidents!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.73,0:11:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, don't be getting\Nahead of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.86,0:11:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a famous detective from Tokyo--\NKogoro Mori!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.24,0:11:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the astronaut?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.04,0:11:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's the one in\Nall those mystery novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Akechi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.62,0:11:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seawater.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.26,0:11:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Approximate time of death\Nwas 30 minutes to an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably died of suffocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.93,0:11:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is that Kawashima-san drowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.39,0:11:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drowned by someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say any more\Nwithout performing an autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Dr. Narumi is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.23,0:11:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, there's a suit jacket\Non the beach outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it belongs to Kawashima-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.49,0:12:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a trail of water here that\Ngoes from the door to the piano
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there's mud and sand\Non Kawashima-san's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.66,0:12:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And judging from the fact that the door\Nand windows were all locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.04,0:12:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that the first few minutes\Nof the cassette tape are blank...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.34,0:12:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did he become so...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.17,0:12:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer probably took Kawashima-san\Nto the ocean during the memorial,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.47,0:12:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,drowned him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.85,0:12:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,dragged the body into this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,locked the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.85,0:12:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turned the tape recorder on,\Nand then exited into the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.77,0:12:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.27,0:12:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, sounds about right to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.61,0:12:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming the door\Nto this room was locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.28,0:12:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a high possibility the killer\Nreturned to the memorial afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since we were at the\Nfront door the whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.16,0:12:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on just a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying the killer's\Nstill among us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.76,0:12:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the killer is in this very room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.18,0:13:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone here see Kawashima-san\Nleave his seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw him. He said he was\Ngoing to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.89,0:13:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anybody see anyone else\Nleave their seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.40,0:13:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if we could remember\Nevery little thing that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.52,0:13:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, did anyone have\Nany grudges with Kawashima-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.53,0:13:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not exactly a grudge,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the person most happy about\Nhis death would be Shimizu-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.28,0:13:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his opponent in the mayoral election!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.91,0:13:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! The same goes for you,\NMayor Kuroiwa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.21,0:13:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, without Kawashima-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.92,0:13:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy's victory would\Npractically be guaranteed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.50,0:13:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as a certain someone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.17,0:13:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't plotting to steal\NKawashima-san's votes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.72,0:13:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.55,0:13:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.80,0:13:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did the killer\Nput the body in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the killer wanted to place\Nthe blame on the cursed piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.90,0:13:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, just how long has\Nthis piano been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been here ever since\NAso-san donated it 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.82,0:14:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aso-san, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.91,0:14:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. His name is even\Non the keyboard lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.96,0:14:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.33,0:14:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. This wasn't here\Nwhen we checked this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.35,0:14:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.97,0:14:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.81,0:14:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did rather well\Nfor himself back in the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he spent lots of money\Non alcohol, women, and gambling...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.86,0:14:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after the mayor died 2 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.94,0:14:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he stopped going out, almost as if\Nhe were afraid of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.78,0:14:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't he a childhood\Nfriend of yours, Mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I suppose you could say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a policeman!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.50,0:14:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're late, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.71,0:15:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I had to look for him,\Nhe wasn't at the police station!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who called for me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.47,0:15:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This gentleman here.\NHis name is Kogoro Mori.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.39,0:15:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the famous--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.39,0:15:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.01,0:15:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astronaut!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.31,0:15:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, it's getting late.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.23,0:15:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can put off collecting information\Nuntil tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.44,0:15:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was no murder.\NIt was Aso-san's curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.65,0:15:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How horrifying...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.99,0:15:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should just burn\Nthat creepy old piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.57,0:15:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Maybe we'd be better off\Nwithout that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.29,0:15:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shuichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your deductions sure\Nsurprised me, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.63,0:15:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He loves playing detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.08,0:15:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone was talking about\Nhow amazing his persuasiveness was!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.80,0:15:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just pretending\Nto be like Detective Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.22,0:15:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always get to see him at work!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.85,0:15:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's just a baby chick\Ncompared to me, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.02,0:16:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we'll head back to the hotel now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.02,0:16:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you later then. Please solve\Nthis case as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather not have to\Nexamine any more bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.94,0:16:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you worry! This'll be a\Npiece of cake with me at the helm!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.62,0:16:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. Not even I really know\Nwhat's going on yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.62,0:16:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That letter said, "begin to disappear"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.21,0:16:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning this isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.05,0:16:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? This murder spree\Nhas yet to continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.76,0:16:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This letter gives warning about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.72,0:16:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shadows disappearing"\Nmeans "being enveloped by light."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.48,0:16:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Light stands for the song played at\Nall the murder scenes--Moonlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.27,0:16:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The song Mr. Aso played\Nin the fire 12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.28,0:16:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the song the mayor played\Nbefore he died 2 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.28,0:16:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Beethoven's\Npiano sonata, Moonlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.95,0:16:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And all three incidents have\Ntaken place beside the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.50,0:17:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two go back to the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.17,0:17:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.04,0:17:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Let's go to the\Ncommunity center too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.51,0:17:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're crazy if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.10,0:17:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spending a night\Nwith a corpse like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.31,0:17:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with a kid, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.64,0:17:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I told you to go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.52,0:17:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Conan-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, who moved the body\Nwithout permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.53,0:17:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt bad for the poor guy,\Nbeing stuck in that position...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.20,0:17:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really shouldn't have,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.87,0:17:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we're not through investigating\Nthe crime scene yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.66,0:17:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? The sheet music's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.61,0:17:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I took that so it\Nwouldn't get lost. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.33,0:17:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid old geezer...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.46,0:17:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.75,0:17:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sheet music is for Moonlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.71,0:17:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.04,0:17:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moonlight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.60,0:17:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing? You suck!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.35,0:18:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this fourth bar is weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourth bar?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.81,0:18:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe this sheet music is actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.32,0:18:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Kawashima-san's dying message...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.69,0:18:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then the killer\Nmight come back for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.74,0:18:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked for you at the hotel,\Nthey said you were all here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.16,0:18:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.75,0:18:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought some dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.62,0:18:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.29,0:18:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we could use some food...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.34,0:18:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're not originally from\Nthis island then, Dr. Narumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I return to Tokyo\Non the weekends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like I work\Nas a part-time doctor here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.22,0:18:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to work\Non a small island like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.14,0:18:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,surrounded by nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.27,0:18:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been working here for 2 years now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.90,0:18:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Mayor Kameyama really die\Nof a heart attack two years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.36,0:18:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He had always had heart troubles...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.03,0:19:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But his face looked rather convulsive,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.12,0:19:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,almost as if he saw\Nsomething horrifying...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.42,0:19:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice anything\Nstrange at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.55,0:19:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.71,0:19:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think one of the windows was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.72,0:19:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A window?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.59,0:19:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe we chalked that up to\Nsomeone forgetting to close it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which window was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.77,0:19:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.77,0:19:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it was this window.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.94,0:19:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.57,0:19:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.61,0:19:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! We lost him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.45,0:19:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was right! He did come back\Nto get this sheet music!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.79,0:19:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! We're going to stay up all night\Nand keep watch over this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.34,0:19:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.17,0:19:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.17,0:19:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.76,0:19:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Mori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.26,0:19:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.68,0:19:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.97,0:20:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure-dono...\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This island's technically part of Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.81,0:20:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. Where did I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.10,0:20:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for the sheet music,\NConan-kun gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.15,0:20:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He also gave me the\Ngist of the situation here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.77,0:20:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All three of them were still awake\Nby the time I arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.36,0:20:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and that old man\Nwere the only ones asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.49,0:20:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're interrogating people\Nover at the town hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.87,0:20:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come give them a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.70,0:20:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.80,0:20:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We really shouldn't have slept there...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.64,0:20:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Well? Did you\Nfigure out who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.64,0:20:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right. There were\N38 people at the memorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.27,0:20:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but when will it be my turn?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem exhausted,\Nso you're scheduled to be last.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.49,0:21:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I think I'll go\Nwash my face in the ladies' room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.70,0:21:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many more interviewees are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.95,0:21:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Including Dr. Narumi, there's six--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.83,0:21:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the mayor's daughter, Reiko Kuroiwa,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.04,0:21:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,her fiancé, Shuichi Murasawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.67,0:21:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,mayoral candidate, Masato Shimizu,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.51,0:21:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the mayor's secretary, Kazuaki Hirata,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.80,0:21:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Ken Nishimoto, who we're\Ninterviewing right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.30,0:21:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's really wasting our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.76,0:21:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't say a word,\Nno matter what we ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.97,0:21:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My instincts say he did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! There's no curse on the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.77,0:21:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as that thing's around,\Nthese murders will keep happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.32,0:21:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mayor...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.77,0:21:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dispose of it immediately!\NYou hear me, Hirata?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.53,0:21:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.48,0:21:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.57,0:21:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had enough of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.70,0:21:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no motive\Nfor killing Kawashima-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.25,0:21:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.46,0:21:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, listen to Reiko-san go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.59,0:21:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been shouting\Nfor 10 minutes straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.54,0:21:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.09,0:22:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're through questioning him,\Nso why isn't Nishimoto-san leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.22,0:22:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.43,0:22:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.19,0:22:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Did Nishimoto-san\Ncome in here just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.40,0:22:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.95,0:22:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap! He took the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.74,0:22:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This music...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.75,0:22:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the second movement of Moonlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.62,0:22:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's it coming from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.25,0:22:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The broadcast room!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.46,0:22:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.80,0:22:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.14,0:22:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't go inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.98,0:22:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the examiners and\Nautopsy team here at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.31,0:22:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.02,0:23:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The autopsy team left for Tokyo\Nthis evening to work on Kawashima-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.65,0:23:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.03,0:23:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! Now, of all times!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.86,0:23:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.66,0:23:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.95,0:23:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.49,0:23:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now this narrows down the suspects\Nto a handful of people!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer is still--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.33,0:23:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the exits to this building\Nare guarded by police.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.79,0:23:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.29,0:23:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it? Who's the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.58,0:23:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears only a few minutes\Nhave passed since the victim's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.62,0:23:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the first 5 minutes and 30 seconds\Nof this tape seem to be blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.59,0:23:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.00,0:23:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was something strange\Nbeneath the body!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.96,0:23:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.96,0:23:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.63,0:23:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheet music?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.39,0:23:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this another dying message\Nfrom the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.39,0:23:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.39,0:23:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had the time and strength\Nto write all this with his own blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.60,0:23:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would've called for help instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.09,0:24:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer probably left\Neach of these behind to--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.05,0:24:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You stay out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.76,0:24:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! That's important evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.72,0:24:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.97,0:24:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the way! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.23,0:24:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing as Beethoven's Moonlight Sonata\Nwas played after each murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.27,0:24:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would seem the same person killed\NKawashima-san and Kuroiwa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.28,0:24:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And judging from the\Namount of blank tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.33,0:24:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroiwa-san must have been killed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,around 6:30, only minutes\Nbefore he was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.79,0:24:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the killer\Nmust have been one of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.75,0:24:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since you were the only ones\Nin the community center at the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.38,0:24:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Excluding Mori-kun and the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.09,0:24:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}that leaves us with Ken Nishimoto-san,\N{\a6}who was the first to find him,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.34,0:24:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Dr. Narumi Asai, who was kind enough\N{\a6}to inspect the body for us just now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.81,0:24:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Kazuaki Hirata-san,\N{\a6}secretary to the late Mayor Kuroiwa,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.31,0:24:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Mayor Kuroiwa's daughter,\N{\a6}Reiko Kuroiwa-san
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.48,0:25:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}and her fiancé, Shuichi Murasawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.77,0:25:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}And then Masato Shimizu-san,\N{\a6}candidate in the mayoral election.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.73,0:25:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! Why am I a suspect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.36,0:25:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been questioning me since 6:20!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.49,0:25:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right,\Nyou couldn't have done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.96,0:25:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you can exclude Dr. Narumi too!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.46,0:25:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been with us since 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.25,0:25:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.55,0:25:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.38,0:25:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that leaves the four men\Nas the only suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.05,0:25:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but I've been\Non this floor since 6:00 or so...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.39,0:25:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have anyone\Nto substantiate this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.06,0:25:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can all vouch for me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.27,0:25:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I went to\Nthe restroom around 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.77,0:25:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Nishimoto-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.53,0:25:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the first person\Nto find Kuroiwa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.53,0:25:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly were you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.49,0:25:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroiwa said he wanted to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.83,0:25:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't ask\Nto see him so you could kill him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.12,0:25:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.41,0:26:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Shimizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.04,0:26:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With Kawashima and my father\Ntaken out of the election,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.88,0:26:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he'd automatically wind up\Nin the mayor's seat!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.47,0:26:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What are you looking at, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.30,0:26:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.05,0:26:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sheet music the killer\Nleft at the murder scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.10,0:26:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is that it's a\Ncoded message from the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.23,0:26:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if there's anything special\Nabout these sharps and flats...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.40,0:26:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the black keys\Non the keyboard. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.69,0:26:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keyboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.45,0:26:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrest this homicidal maniac\Nbefore he kills anyone else--
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.91,0:26:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better watch out. You're next.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.04,0:26:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.08,0:26:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This code's easy if\Nyou know how to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.83,0:26:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's based on the notes that\Ncorrespond with specific piano keys
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.21,0:26:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you arrange the letters of the\Nalphabet across a piano keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.88,0:26:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this, the music found where\NKawashima-san was killed says,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.68,0:27:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Better watch out. You're next."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.31,0:27:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.19,0:27:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.02,0:27:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does the other sheet music say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.86,0:27:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.53,0:27:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Extinguished is the anger\Nof the hellfire."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.28,0:27:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The anger of the hellfire?!\NCould it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.70,0:27:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that pianist who killed himself\Nin a fire 12 years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.29,0:27:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's him! Keiji Aso's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.46,0:27:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No he isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.72,0:27:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bones found in the ashes\Nmatched his dental records--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.55,0:27:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he's most certainly dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.93,0:27:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything was completely scorched.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.97,0:27:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that was left was some\Nsheet music in a fireproof safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.15,0:27:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheet music?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.94,0:27:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where? Where is this sheet music?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.65,0:27:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the community center storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.86,0:27:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the key to the storeroom's\Nback at the station--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.66,0:27:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then go get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.65,0:27:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.70,0:28:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Officer! I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.00,0:28:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.37,0:28:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, did Aso-san really\Nset his own house on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.63,0:28:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there were four eyewitnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.72,0:28:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our previous mayor, Kameyama-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.63,0:28:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayor Kuroiwa, Nishimoto-san,\Nand Kawashima-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.93,0:28:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were those four connected in any way?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.68,0:28:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all classmates,\Nincluding Aso-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.19,0:28:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about that Murasawa guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.77,0:28:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He showed up on the island 3 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.07,0:28:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He and the mayor's daughter Reiko-san\Nwere engaged not too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.86,0:28:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mayor opposed it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.24,0:28:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Hirata,\Nthe mayor's secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.12,0:28:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's suspicious if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.37,0:28:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not quite sure what the deal was,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.42,0:28:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he was always sneaking\Naround with Kawashima-san
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.71,0:28:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the community center.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.80,0:28:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Shimizu?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.96,0:28:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a strong sense of justice and\Nhe's very popular with the fishermen!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.64,0:29:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you out of questions, Akechi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.47,0:29:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.35,0:29:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's odd!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.31,0:29:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could swear it was\Naround here somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.27,0:29:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. You've been\Nlooking for over an hour now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.61,0:29:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go! Here's the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.70,0:29:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.04,0:29:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran...?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.66,0:29:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You took too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.87,0:29:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone grew tired of waiting\Nso they went home!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.33,0:29:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the suspects left?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.67,0:29:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.67,0:29:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer's last message said that\Nthe hellfire's anger was extinguished,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.76,0:29:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they figured there\Nwould be no more murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.14,0:29:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiots!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.68,0:29:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the 1st and 2nd movements\Nof Moonlight have been played
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.89,0:29:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at each of the murder scenes so far!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.89,0:29:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moonlight has one movement left!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.44,0:29:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to check out\Nthe community center!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.90,0:29:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.57,0:30:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about curious, Conan-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.95,0:30:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.45,0:30:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hold on, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.16,0:30:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you just hear a strange sound\Ncome from the piano room?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.62,0:30:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.21,0:30:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.13,0:30:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.80,0:30:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Murasawa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.64,0:30:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.85,0:30:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The storeroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.31,0:30:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.73,0:30:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer! Go call Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.44,0:30:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.28,0:30:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the 3rd movement played?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.62,0:30:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's 30 minutes per side on this tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.53,0:30:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which means Nishimoto-san died\Nwithin the last 30 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.54,0:30:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.54,0:30:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's some more sheet music\Nat Nishimoto-san's feet!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.25,0:31:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it say this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.05,0:31:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Will."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.38,0:31:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's his will?!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.13,0:31:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.55,0:31:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.56,0:31:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the will,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.89,0:31:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he regretted killing Mr. Kawashima\Nand Mr. Kuroiwa...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.39,0:31:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto killed the two of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.06,0:31:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He apparently didn't want an old mistake\Nthey made to be made known.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.44,0:31:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"They" refers to Mr. Kameyama,\Nwho died 2 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.78,0:31:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kawashima and Mr. Kuroiwa,\Nwho were just killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.70,0:31:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Nishimoto, who hanged himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.70,0:31:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Mr. Aso, who killed himself\N12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.62,0:31:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pianist too?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.04,0:31:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is that they did something,\Nusing this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.96,0:31:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Nishimoto-san was afraid\Ntheir old secret would get out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.42,0:31:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he broke into the storeroom\Nto destroy the sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.63,0:31:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But unable to find the music and\Ndriven into a psychological corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.47,0:31:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.39,0:31:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.39,0:31:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to hang yourself\Nwithout something to support you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.81,0:31:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't put it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.15,0:31:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.11,0:32:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I doubt there's anyone who would\Ngo and write their own will in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.61,0:32:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying the murderer\Nis somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.16,0:32:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw some suspicious people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.99,0:32:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.87,0:32:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two people in the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.66,0:32:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One broke a window and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.87,0:32:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other was that Murasawa guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.88,0:32:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone beat him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.25,0:32:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi's treating him\Nin the piano room right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.75,0:32:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.09,0:32:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you say that sooner?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.43,0:32:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.72,0:32:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still haven't found\NMr. Aso's sheet music?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.43,0:32:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was 12 years ago. There's no way\Nfor me to remember where we put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.40,0:32:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he still unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.36,0:32:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I think he may have\Nsuffered a concussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.78,0:32:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Kuroiwa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.36,0:32:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was Murasawa-san\Ndoing here this late anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.33,0:32:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.21,0:32:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.37,0:32:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your hands off Shuichi's stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.79,0:33:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.17,0:33:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me! But it\Nwas important to Shuichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.13,0:33:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a tuning hammer,\Nused to tune pianos.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.18,0:33:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was the one who...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.64,0:33:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Bring all the suspects\Nto the town hall at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.68,0:33:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.77,0:33:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.28,0:33:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the town hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.36,0:33:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The suspicious person\Nwho ran out of this room
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.24,0:33:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was looking for something\Nunder the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.78,0:33:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.87,0:33:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, a hidden panel! Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.34,0:33:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drugs!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.09,0:33:48.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukikage Island Town Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.97,0:33:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the methods\Nemployed in all three murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.34,0:33:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they are all clearly\Nthe work of the same person!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.14,0:33:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi and Reiko Kuroiwa-san\Nhave confirmed alibis
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.10,0:33:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are no longer suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.85,0:34:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are no alibis\Nfor the secretary Hirata-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.81,0:34:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the mayoral candidate Shimizu-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.53,0:34:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor for Murasawa-san, who is\Ncurrently resting at the clinic...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.11,0:34:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is one of these three!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.28,0:34:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi. Is Murasawa-san\Nstill unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.58,0:34:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Reiko-san is looking after him,\Nbut he has yet to regain consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.62,0:34:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something nagging at me,\Nbut what could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.13,0:34:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I saw the code of blood\Nleft at the scene of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.34,0:34:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.09,0:34:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The photos taken from where\NMr. Kuroiwa was murdered are ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.01,0:34:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Place them on that desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.60,0:34:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.31,0:34:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that light by Kuroiwa-san's neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.94,0:34:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's off in the picture\Nwhere he's been moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.23,0:34:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, may I buy some juice?\NI'm thirsty...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.82,0:34:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose that'd be alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.08,0:34:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.83,0:35:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.58,0:35:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's some white powder\Non your sleeves.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.04,0:35:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.05,0:35:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money from all over the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.05,0:35:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fond of foreign countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.18,0:35:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.06,0:35:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.94,0:35:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found the sheet music\NAso-san left behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.40,0:35:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see that!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.78,0:35:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"To my son, Seiji."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.78,0:35:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.99,0:35:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come to think of it,\NAso-san had a son too...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.38,0:35:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He fell seriously ill when he was little\Nand had to be hospitalized...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.46,0:35:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe Seiji was his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.92,0:35:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seiji?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.55,0:35:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.35,0:36:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait! Where do you\Nthink you're going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.23,0:36:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.49,0:36:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the killer dragged\NKawashima-san into the piano room
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.61,0:36:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after drowning him!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.99,0:36:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The meaning of the music\Nplayed at the murder scenes!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.45,0:36:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the mystery behind\Nthe code written in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.37,0:36:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it!\NThat's the one who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.38,0:36:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Mori received a\Nletter from a dead man
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.96,0:36:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then headed to Tsukikage Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.13,0:36:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The letter's author was Keiji Aso,\Na pianist who murdered his family,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.81,0:36:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lit his house on fire, and died\Nwhile playing the Moonlight piano sonata.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.73,0:36:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The 1st murder happened on the night\Nof the memorial for Mr. Kameyama,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.61,0:36:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the previous mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.61,0:36:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideo Kawashima was\Nfound dead in the piano room,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.86,0:36:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while the first movement\Nof Moonlight played.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.11,0:37:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second murder took place\Nas the second movement played.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.12,0:37:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was the current mayor,\NTatsuji Kuroiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.70,0:37:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The number of suspects was\Nnarrowed down to six people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.12,0:37:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third murder was\Nthat of Ken Nishimoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.17,0:37:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed in a manner\Nthat made it look like suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.09,0:37:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"To my son, Seiji."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.05,0:37:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.51,0:37:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the killer dragged\NKawashima-san into the piano room
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.64,0:37:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after drowning him!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.18,0:37:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The meaning of the music\Nplayed at the murder scenes!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.52,0:37:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the mystery behind\Nthe code written in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.69,0:37:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it!\NThat's the one who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.95,0:37:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big idea, rushing here\Nto the broadcast room like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.20,0:37:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.20,0:37:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.33,0:37:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got no choice! I'll have to\Nuse the old man's voice for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.58,0:37:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One shot of this\NAnesthetic Watch Gun and...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.83,0:38:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hirata-san and Shimizu-san will\Nhave to come to the mainland with us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.05,0:38:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.01,0:38:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.63,0:38:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first incident, in which\NMr. Kawashima was drowned
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.81,0:38:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and dragged into the community center's\Npiano room last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.52,0:38:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second incident,\Nin which Mr. Kuroiwa was murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.94,0:38:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the broadcast room\Nthis very night...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.90,0:38:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third incident, which also\Ntook place this very night,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.94,0:38:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in which Mr. Nishimoto\Nwas killed in the storeroom
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.78,0:38:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in such a way to make\Nit look like a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.28,0:38:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones without alibis for\Nthese three incidents are you two
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.62,0:38:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Murasawa-san,\Nwho is resting at the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.83,0:38:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to do this, but we'll\Nhave to watch you tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.96,0:38:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.96,0:38:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost everything about the murders\Non this island, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.05,0:38:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! You're in the broadcast room?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.05,0:38:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, the person who beat Murasawa-san\Nunconscious in the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.60,0:38:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be you, Hirata-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.22,0:38:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.60,0:38:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hirata-san suffered\Nthe injury on his left hand
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.98,0:38:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when he broke the window and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.82,0:38:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were also the suspicious\Nperson we saw last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.86,0:39:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what was he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.73,0:39:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was making deals with\NMr. Kawashima in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.41,0:39:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drug deals.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.32,0:39:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drugs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.45,0:39:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hirata-san used a\Nhidden panel in the piano
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.12,0:39:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to trade drugs he bought overseas\Nfor large sums of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.29,0:39:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! So that's why they were at the\Ncommunity center every single night!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.55,0:39:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason Hirata-san always\Nclaimed the piano was cursed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.64,0:39:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was to keep people\Nfrom getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.64,0:39:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably assaulted\NMurasawa-san and escaped
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.69,0:39:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because Murasawa-san saw him taking\Nback the drugs he had left there!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.02,0:39:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you killed Mr. Kawashima
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.32,0:39:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because you were having a dispute\Nwith him about the deals?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.32,0:39:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.32,0:39:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hirata-san has nothing\Nto do with the three murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.37,0:39:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he was the murderer, he wouldn't\Nhave killed anyone in the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.45,0:39:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the room where\Nhe left the drugs, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.70,0:39:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is Murasawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.00,0:39:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.79,0:40:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not the killer either.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.34,0:40:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the killer wrote a\Nwill to make it look a suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.68,0:40:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but didn't place an object\Nto stand on in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.64,0:40:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was because the murderer bolted\Nwhen Ran and the others showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.10,0:40:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been impossible\Nto enter the piano room afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.85,0:40:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.02,0:40:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So far, our image of the\Nkiller has been that of a man,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.48,0:40:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because all three murders\Nrequired someone with strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.86,0:40:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And someone without an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.94,0:40:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only suspect left is Shimizu-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.78,0:40:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, we need to look\Nat the second murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.37,0:40:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We assumed Kuroiwa-san was killed\Nonly minutes before he was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.75,0:40:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you'll remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.83,0:40:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the blood code didn't\Ncome off when Conan fell on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.84,0:40:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At room temperature, it takes 15\Nto 30 minutes for human blood to dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.01,0:40:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that blood was dry,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.26,0:40:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even though he was supposedly\Nkilled only minutes before.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.22,0:41:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It was a trick the killer\Ndid to alter the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.19,0:41:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.11,0:41:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But only the first 5 and a half minutes\Nof the tape were blank!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.15,0:41:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Automatic tape reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.95,0:41:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer played the 2nd side\Nof the tape, which had no music on it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.16,0:41:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gained 30 extra minutes\Nby using tape reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.12,0:41:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please have a look at the photographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.20,0:41:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a button lit\Nnear Kuroiwa-san's neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.46,0:41:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the light is off\Njust after his body is moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.67,0:41:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's proof that the killer\Nturned it off when you weren't looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.76,0:41:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I remember correctly,\Nthe one who approached the body was--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.88,0:41:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.43,0:41:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who got near the body,\Naside from the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.81,0:41:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who faked\Nthe estimated time of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.15,0:41:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was the one who inspected\Nthe body--you, Dr. Narumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.70,0:41:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true, is it, Dr. Narumi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.74,0:41:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You drowned Kawashima-san and\Ndragged him into the piano room
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.29,0:41:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to send the coroners\Nback to the mainland,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.41,0:42:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since they wouldn't be able\Nto examine an unnatural death here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.96,0:42:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the reason you put blank space\Nat the start of each tape
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.67,0:42:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was so that you could throw us off\Nby faking the time of the 2nd murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.05,0:42:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doing this, you altered\NKuroiwa-san's time of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.18,0:42:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,thereby creating an alibi for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.68,0:42:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mori-kun! You just\Nsaid the killer was a man!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.06,0:42:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The motive for the murders\Nextends 12 years back.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.94,0:42:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.56,0:42:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back to the incident in which pianist\NKeiji Aso and his family were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.78,0:42:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.99,0:42:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawashima-san, Nishimoto-san,\NKuroiwa-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.78,0:42:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the previous mayor, Kameyama-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.57,0:42:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They used Aso-san's\Ninternational performances
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.71,0:42:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as opportunities to buy and sell drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.04,0:42:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then Aso-san said he\Nrefused to help them any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.55,0:42:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afraid their secret would get out,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.17,0:42:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they shut him and his family inside\Nhis house and set it on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.31,0:43:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all written in the sheet music\Nthat survived that fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.23,0:43:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the confession letter\Nthat Aso-san wrote for his child...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.23,0:43:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A son?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.23,0:43:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had a son in a Tokyo hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.03,0:43:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One named Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.86,0:43:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seiji? It couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.87,0:43:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Narumi's real name is Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.04,0:43:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was Keiji Aso's son, Seiji Aso!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.70,0:43:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.91,0:43:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asai is probably his\Nfoster family's last name.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.05,0:43:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was all to avenge his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.47,0:43:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! The killer's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.47,0:43:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.01,0:43:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.47,0:43:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know where he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.60,0:43:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The place where Aso Keiji's donated\Npiano is kept--the community center!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.15,0:43:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.03,0:43:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.95,0:43:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.54,0:44:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's written in this sheet\Nmusic your dad left for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.96,0:44:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he wants you\Nto live an honest life!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.00,0:44:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I had known that sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.09,0:44:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find out about your father\Nif you haven't read this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.93,0:44:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always had my suspicions\Nabout my foster father.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.85,0:44:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After graduating from medical school,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.35,0:44:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to this island\Nas a woman doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.31,0:44:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't say on my license\Nhow to pronounce my name, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.86,0:44:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was sweating bullets\Nwhen they started questioning people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.20,0:44:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They would've found out\NI was really a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.28,0:44:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's why you\Nstayed with us that night--
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.37,0:44:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you could have them\Nquestion you last.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.87,0:44:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I told Kameyama, the previous mayor,\Nthat I was Aso's son,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.75,0:44:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he suddenly grew fearful\Nand told me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.71,0:44:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He finished it all off by falling\Nlifeless from a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.72,0:45:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was when I played my father's\Nfavorite piece, Moonlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.89,0:45:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a farewell song for him that I came up\Nwith the idea for these murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.01,0:45:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seiji! Let's get out of here!\NWe can still make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.27,0:45:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.40,0:45:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These hands are as\Nbloodstained as theirs are.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.62,0:45:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.66,0:45:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.24,0:45:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.20,0:45:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.00,0:45:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.17,0:45:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.38,0:45:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's playing it. Inside the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.60,0:45:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Murasawa-san missed Keiji Aso,\Nthe pianist,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.56,0:45:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he apparently tuned\Nhis piano on occasion...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.82,0:45:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the night he was assaulted, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.74,0:46:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did Dr. Narumi warn us\Nabout the murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.95,0:46:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My only guess is that it was actually\Na letter of challenge to Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.62,0:46:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she wanted to be\Nstopped from killing...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.37,0:46:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what did the code\Nthat Dr. Narumi played say?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.92,0:46:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I already forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.83,0:46:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your expression says otherwise!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.22,0:46:31.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Little Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.11,0:46:48.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just my imagination {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.66,0:46:58.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Playing with threads around my finger\Nwhile drinking lukewarm tea{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.00,0:47:07.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's walk lightly\Nto the bossa nova rhythm{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.47,0:47:12.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The puzzle pieces are in my hands{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.56,0:47:18.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.77,0:47:28.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was in the same place last week\Nbut with different clothes{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.82,0:47:35.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Step by step,\Nthere's no reason to be anxious{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.83,0:47:42.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Case by case,\NI don't care if you laugh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.75,0:47:52.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beyond the countless days,\Nshe's waiting for me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.51,0:47:56.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I gotta go my own way {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.30,0:48:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me the car\NAyumi-chan got in
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.76,0:48:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,belonged to those kidnappers\Nwho're killing little girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.49,0:48:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Ayumi-chan!\NWe're coming to save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.68,0:48:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.86,0:48:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumi-chan's Abduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.71,0:48:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.03,0:48:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A School Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.89,0:48:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is a little different from usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.56,0:48:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
